parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Oil leakage from the transfer case
loud thumping noise
wheels locking up
vehicle spinning out of control
fluids slowly leaking from the bottom of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or fail to engage gears, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling
transmission slipping into gear
not engaging immediately when put in gear
transmission bolt needing to be tightened frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearings can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Driver's front and rear wheel bearings failed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor service from dealerships can lead to delays in repairs, verbal abuse, and a lack of respect for customers, which can cause frustration and stress.
symptoms: Delayed repairs
verbal abuse
lack of respect for customers
refusal to honor warranty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause unexpected and sudden activation of the brakes, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard and pulsates
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the vehicle may spin or lose control
the ABS system engages on dry pavement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt retractor can cause the passenger lap belt to remain extended, potentially leading to entanglement or obstruction, which can increase the risk of injury or accident.
symptoms: The passenger lap belt does not automatically retract after being fully extended
the belt remains stuck in the extended position
the belt is difficult to retract manually.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side safety belt can cause the belt to malfunction or break, potentially leading to serious injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The driver's side safety belt fails to restrain the driver
the belt breaks or tears
the belt buckle fails to latch or unlatch properly
the belt webbing is damaged or frayed.
